The yogurt market can be segmented based on product type, flavor, and distribution channel. In terms of product type, there is a growing demand for Greek yogurt due to its perceived health benefits and creamy texture. Regular yogurt remains a staple product in many households. The popularity of frozen yogurt as a dessert alternative has been on the rise, especially among health-conscious consumers. Drinkable yogurt is gaining traction as a convenient, on-the-go snack option. In terms of flavor, classic options like strawberry and blueberry continue to be popular, while newer flavors like vanilla and peach are also becoming favorites among consumers. In the distribution channel segment, supermarkets and hypermarkets dominate sales due to their wide product range and accessibility. Convenience stores also play a significant role in reaching consumers looking for quick and easy purchases. The online retail segment is experiencing exponential growth, driven by the convenience of ordering from home and the increasing digitalization of shopping habits.

